---

## ğŸ’¬ Notes / What I Learned

- **XOR with a repeating key (Crib Dragging Technique)** is a common technique in CTFs â€” easy to crack with known plaintext.
- Knowing just part of the flag (like `ctflearn{`) can be powerful enough to break the cipher.
- Escape characters in `bytes` are just decimal values and can be handled normally in Python.
- Always test if the cipher repeats â€” repeating keys usually signal weak encryption.

